Results.ReviewText:
My wife and I have been Gold Blend devotees for many years but the new recipe has changed that. Why Nescafe have taken it upon themselves to change a tried and tested product is beyond me. The new recipe has microgrounds added but for me they add nothing to the taste which is very bland compared to the previous recipe. I have read that the intention is to provide more of a "Barista style" coffee but Nescafe already provide such a blend for those who choose it. I feel it is misleading not to highlight that there is a new recipe and 'original' should not be applied in any way.
I would also add that the new jars do not provide enough distinction between the varieties and we accidentally bought a jar of decaff. The tops are now all the same colour and the labels very similar.
I am pleased to say that we have found another product that is far superior and have switched to that.
Results.Title: Bye Bye Nescafe it was nice knowing you

Results.ReviewText: I have just started drinking the newly branded Gold Blend, after probably 20 years or more drinking the 'original'. Whilst I don't necessarily agree there is no aroma (at least it still smells nice when a new pack is opened), the grainy, black 'sludge' as described by many others on this platform, is most unwelcome. It's back to the dark ages when we habitually left the final mouthful in the cup to avoid the dregs. Well the dregs are back! Not impressed I'm afraid.

Results.ReviewText: Love the new branding the colours are a lot sleeker and suit the coffee title better however having being a gold blend drinker for many years now I’m not sure of the coffee. This is my first jar since you rebranded and I hope it’s just a bad batch, maybe? but there is a definite change to the consistency of the coffee. Whilst it looks great on making it once it starts to cool there seems to be a darker powdery like residue which is obvious once you get to the bottom of the cup. This is a tad off putting for me personally and so I’m not finishing my much loved gold blend. The flavour isn’t up to its usual standard and tastes a little wushu washy. I do hope this is just a one off and that my next jar is back to its 5 star best.
